    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1077"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1077">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 831.415 A/28b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President of Venezuela</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Permit me to add to the messages of cordial friendship which are being conveyed
                    to Your Excellency and the Government and people of Venezuela by the special
                    embassy of the United States, my most sincere congratulations and those of the
                    Government of the United States on this memorable occasion when the people of
                    your country are celebrating the centennial anniversay of their independence,
                    and to wish for your country continued prosperity. I also oiler Your Excellency
                    personally the assurance of my high regard and best wishes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
